 beautiful widow who delivers her people from the invading Assyrians by gaining the confidence of their commander, Holofernes, and cutting off his head while he is asleep; without their commander, the Assyrians are duly routed. This has been a perennially popular Jewish name. In the English-speaking world it was taken up in the 16th century, having been in occasional use among Gentiles before this: for example, it was borne by a niece of William the Conqueror. It enjoyed great popularity between the 1940s and the 1960s. Today's notable bearers include the American novelist  Judith Krantz  (  b. 1928 ) and the Scottish composer  Judith Weir  (  b. 1954 )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Judith Montanolier was born in 0995, in Normandy, France as the daughter of Guillaume de Montpellier II. She married Thurstan le Goz Viscomte d'Avranches about 1024, in Avranches, Manche, Normandy, France. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She was buried in Normandy, France."},"et":{"995–":"0995–Surnud","0995–Female":"0995–Surnud","0989–1041":"0989–1041","1017–1066":"1017–1066","1025–1082":"1025–1082","0950–0999":"0950–0999","1066":"1066","1041":"1041","1082":"1082","13 October 1025":"19. oktoober 1025","1007":"1007","1006":"1006","0950":"0950","1017":"1017","1005":"1005","0995":"0995","995":"0995","about 1017":"umbes 1017","1025":"1025","about 1024":"umbes 1024","0989":"0989","0999":"0999","Tilleul-en-Ange, Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Normandie, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Normandy, France":"Normandie, Prantsusmaa","Avranches, Manche, Normandy, France":"Avranches, Manche, Normandie, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"995–":"0995–Kuollut","0995–Female":"0995–Kuollut","0989–1041":"0989–1041","1017–1066":"1017–1066","1025–1082":"1025–1082","0950–0999":"0950–0999","1066":"1066","1041":"1041","1082":"1082","13 October 1025":"19. lokakuuta 1025","1007":"1007","1006":"1006","0950":"0950","1017":"1017","1005":"1005","0995":"0995","995":"0995","about 1017":"noin 1017","1025":